te of mass loss from the BH sub-system is\napproximately independent of the stellar mass ratio (m_2/m_1) and the total\nmass ratio (M_2/M_1) (in the range m_2/m_1 >~ 10 and M_2/M_1 ~ 10^{-2}, where\nm_1, m_2 are the masses of individual low-mass and high-mass particles\nrespectively, and M_1, M_2 are the corresponding total masses).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 11 Apr 2013 19:21:22 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-15"}
