lli(\\fA):S(\\fA))$ for general\n$\\fA$ and $S$. For $\\fA=\\C$ and general $S$, we further compute the latter\ngroups in terms of algebraic differential forms. We prove that the map\n$HC_n(\\Gami(\\C):I_{S(\\C)})\\to HC_n(\\cB:J_S)$ is an isomorphism in many cases.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 11 Apr 2013 23:44:06 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 6 May 2013 23:11:11 GMT"}],"update_date":"2013-05-08"}
